The streams module
==================

    >>> from pysyte import streams
    >>> assert 'handle streams' in streams.__doc__

Printing to stdout
------------------

pysyte.streams offers 2 functions which print to stdout/stderr

    >>> from pysyte.streams import print_out
    >>> from pysyte.streams import print_err

    >>> print_out("Hello World")
    Hello World
    >>> print_err("Goodbye World")
    Goodbye World



Swallowing stdout
-----------------

    >>> from io import StringIO
    >>> stream = StringIO()
    >>> with streams.swallow_stdout(stream):
    ...     print('Hello World')
    ...
    >>> assert stream.getvalue() == 'Hello World\n'

Simpler - use default stream
    >>> with streams.swallow_stdout() as stream:
    ...     print('Hello World')
    ...
    >>> assert stream.getvalue() == 'Hello World\n'


std
===

streams provides a simpler interface to sys.stdin, sys.stdout, sys.stderr

    >>> std = streams.std
    >>> std.out("Hello"); std.err("World")
    Hello
    World
    >>> std.write("Hello World")
    Hello World

#   >>> key = std.in(1)
    >>> assert std.in_fileno() == 0

